text: Val-de-Moder is a commune. It is in Grand Est in the Bas-Rhin department in northeast France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Pfaffenhoffen (the seat), Uberach and La Walck.Arrêté préfectoral 7 December 2015 On 1 January 2019, the former commune of Ringeldorf became a part of Val-de-Moder.Arrêté préfectoral 19 December 2018 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Bas-Rhin
title: Val-de-Moder
